        <!-- The Purpose -->
        <div class="card">
            <h2>üéØ The True Purpose</h2>
            
            <div class="purpose-box">
                <h3>Fortress is a safety app for people in dangerous situations.</h3>
                <p>It's disguised as everyday apps (a recipe collection or period tracker) so that it won't raise suspicion if someone's phone is checked. The app allows users to safely document incidents, plan for emergencies, and access wellness resources ‚Äî all hidden behind what appears to be a normal, innocent app.</p>
            </div>

            <h3>Who It's For:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Survivors of domestic violence documenting abuse</li>
                <li>People planning to safely leave dangerous relationships</li>
                <li>Anyone who needs to keep sensitive personal information hidden</li>
                <li>Advocates and professionals supporting survivors</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="info-box">
                <strong>Why Your Testing Matters:</strong><br>
                Your feedback will directly help people in crisis. Every bug you find, every confusing interaction you report, every suggestion you make could help someone stay safe. Thank you for being part of this.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- The Disguises -->
        <div class="card">
            <h2>üé≠ The Disguise Apps</h2>
            <p>The app appears as one of two innocent-looking apps:</p>

            <div class="disguise-tabs">
                <div class="tab tab-savor">
                    <div class="icon">üç≥</div>
                    <strong>Savor</strong>
                    <p>Recipe Collection</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tab tab-bloom">
                    <div class="icon">üå∏</div>
                    <strong>Bloom</strong>
                    <p>Period Tracker</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p>Both disguise apps are <strong>fully functional</strong> ‚Äî you can actually browse recipes or track periods. This makes the disguise completely believable. The app icon on the home screen also changes based on which disguise is selected.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- How to Access -->
        <div class="card">
            <h2>üîê Accessing the Hidden Features</h2>
            
            <div class="steps">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">1</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h4>Open the App</h4>
                        <p>Launch Savor or Bloom. It will look and work like a normal app.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">2</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h4>Long-Press the Logo</h4>
                        <p>Find the app logo/title at the top of the screen. Press and hold it for 5 seconds. You'll see a subtle progress indicator.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">3</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h4>"Premium Features" Appears</h4>
                        <p>A passcode screen will appear, disguised as a "Premium Features" unlock. This looks like a normal in-app purchase to anyone watching.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">4</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h4>Enter Passcode</h4>
                        <p>For testing, the default passcode is: <strong>1234</strong> (or whatever you set during onboarding). This unlocks the secure Fortress area.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <strong>üé≠ Decoy Passcode:</strong><br>
                The app also supports a "decoy" passcode. If someone is forced to open the app, entering the decoy code shows a fake premium features page instead of the real secure content. Test this in Settings!
            </div>
        </div>

